Rating: 0
Made this cake 2x - yesterday and in 2011. Modifications to 2013 cake resulted in light cake w/ subtle and complimentary flavors. Got rave reviews from Iranian/American and Polish/German friends who do not like overly sweet desserts. Used standard baking practices - ingredients at room temp, preheated oven; frosting bowl, whip and ingredients at cold temp (kept mine outside in 20deg F for an hour). Used the following modifications: 5 egg whites, 1/2 tsp cream of tartar, and NO added sugar in egg whites; 3 Tbsp water + 3 Tbsp rosewater, 1 tsp ground cardamom (did not like whole seeds in cake); liked the tsp lemon peel for the subtle citrus "zing". Beat yolks, then added oil until incorporated, then added waters. Baked in parchment-lined 10x15 sheet pan for 15-17 mins then cut for three (3) 5"x10" layers. For frosting: used 1 Tbsp rosewater, 1 tsp ground cardamom. First time I made this cake, I used grocery store roses to make candied petals - dried overnight, no problems. Second time, I used coarsely chopped toasted pistachio on sides. Cake was just slightly chilled when served and I found it was quite nice that way. Looking forward to make this cake again!

