Rating: 4
I have reviewed this recipe before but have made it a few more times with increasingly good results. I made three batches of this cake for a friend's wedding and found a nice little tip. I ran out of superfine baking sugar and used powdered sugar in the egg whites (which I've increased to 5).It definitely made a difference. There was much more loft in the last cake. I also added a 1/4 tsp cream of tartar. When folding the the whites into the flour mixture, I've found it doesn't need to be all the way blended. This also helps keep the whites fluffy. Also I agree about not greasing the pans. Helps keep it lifted. Use parchment on the bottom and if the cake doesn't pull away just run a knife along the top to loosen. I get nothing but raves when I make this cake. Please try it! You wont be disappointed!

