Rating: 3
A beautiful & delicious cake. Took two tries to get the cake part right. My first attempt, the layers fell flat as well, then I realized this is a pretty traditional chiffon-style cake. You are NOT supposed to grease a pan when making a chiffon cake (just like angel food). The cake needs to grab onto the sides of the pan to keep its height, so that was a bad instruction. Put parchment in the bottom, don't grease the pan, & the layers come out beautifully, once cooled. I also increased the proportions for the cake by half, so as to have slightly higher layers. I would DEFINITELY make it again, with the modified recipe. I also saw cupcakes with this recipe elsewhere on the internet -- very cute!

