Rating: 4
I've made this cake numerous times, all to rave reviews! Absolutely crush the cardamom; doing so spreads the flavor through the cake without overpowering the lemon (as ground cardamom does), and eliminates the risk of someone breaking a tooth! Yes, more cardamom, yes, more rosewater, and I love how the saffron threads stain the cream, so I don't strain them. I cut the sugar and skip the candying, using fresh, FRAGRANT rose petals, which have their own captivating sweetness. Pistachios are not a must, but they're a lovely addition. For gluten- and wheat-free cake eaters, use 2 parts Brown Rice Flour and 1 part Quinoa Flour. Also, I make it a rectangular three-layer cake (Frankensteined from two 9-inch square pans)--even more decadent an unusual, and easier to make a beautiful half-recipe cake or several mini-cakes. There's never a morsel leftover!

